ーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーー

What's that saying? Speak of the devil... oh,
there!\n< Burdan >

Lord Tim... it's been a while... well, a few days
since we last met...\n< Serena >

Come on, come on, don't just stand there, come
over here.\n< Burdan >

Just kidding, just kidding, today is Tim-kun's
birthday! Yay!\n< Burdan >

I haven't heard about this. Is that true, Lord
Tim?\n< Serena >
Ah... yes. Uh, heh... heh.\n< Tim >
How old are you turning this year, Tim-kun?\n< Burdan >

I'm not exactly sure. About 13... I think.
Maybe...\n< Tim >
By the way, I'm 12. Remember that, will you?\n< Burdan >

What's the matter? Not feeling it? Come on, let's
celebrate more!\n< Burdan >

No, I've heard that some regions have such
celebrations.\n< Serena >

In my family, we don't particularly celebrate
individual birthdays.\n< Serena >

Therefore, I'm at a loss when you tell me to
celebrate. What should I do?\n< Serena >

Eh? Well, I've never had a celebration for my
birthday either!\n< Burdan >

Ah... me neither... nothing special for
birthdays...\n< Tim >

...Looks like we've got three birthday novices
here...\n< Burdan >

Anyway, from what I've heard, you're supposed to
eat and drink a lot, and then dance!\n< Burdan >
...Ah, no, I've never really danced before...\n< Tim >
Sorry, I'll just watch from here...\n< Tim >

Fine then. Come here Serena. You can dance, can't
you?\n< Burdan >

Besides, Serena-san is pregnant... she shouldn't
do any strenuous exercise...\n< Tim >

Alright alright, may I have the pleasure of your
hand, madam...! And one, two-, and one, two-!\n< Burdan >

Ngh, you fool, your steps are all over the
place...\n< Serena >

Shishishi, I've never really danced properly
before either!\n< Burdan >

Like this. Move your feet... yes. Place your hands
on your hips, right, right, left.\n< Serena >

Shishishi, oh, this is quite fun, isn't it? Then
like this, and there!\n< Burdan >
Ngh! You fool! Don't bump into my stomach!\n< Serena >

Shishi? It's Serena's fault for having such a huge
belly. There's a limit to how much I can avoid it.\n< Burdan >

Ngh! You fool! Consider the difference in our
stride!\n< Serena >

Shishi? Ah, my bad, my bad, I've got long legs,
you see.\n< Burdan >
That is, your breathing is... in sync, sort of.\n< Tim >

Ah, well, that's because we've exercised together
so many times...\n< Burdan >
Ah, no, it's nothing, Lord Tim.\n< Serena >

To think you'd show up out of the blue, and on a
birthday no less...\n< Tim >

I'm happy to see Serena-san, but... I can't fully
enjoy myself in this state of limbo...\n< Tim >
...What's going to happen to me from now on?\n< Tim >

At first, we were supposed to start a postal
service together... You said it was to earn money
for that... and it just went on and on...\n< Tim >

Poison is absolutely out of the question. No
matter how much money it makes. No, first of all,
are we really making that much money?\n< Tim >
You haven't shown your face or worked for days...\n< Tim >

I know what you're up to, Burdan-kun. You're
trying to sweet-talk me to cover up something
that's not going your way...\n< Tim >

Then maybe today is my chance? Serena-san is here
too.\n< Tim >

If I tell Burdan-kun now that I want to quit...
Serena-san will surely take my side.\n< Tim >
That's right, I'll say it. I'll say it...\n< Tim >

I'll open this door and say it right away. Burdan-
kun! I'm stopping this!... like that.\n< Tim >

If I can just get that one sentence out, the rest
will follow with momentum...\n< Tim >

Let's calm down a bit... Go through the rehearsal
in my head one more time...\n< Tim >

It's okay. Even if it's a bit strange, Serena-san
will back me up.\n< Tim >
This is the only chance I have. Now, now...\n< Tim >

She left...? Well, Burdan-kun aside, Serena-san
wouldn't just...\n< Tim >
I wonder where she went.\n< Tim >

Ah, Burdan...kun. Welcome back... I was surprised
because both of you were gone...\n< Tim >

My bad, my bad. We both needed to use the
restroom. We went to look for one outside.\n< Burdan >

I wonder how far Serena went? I think she'll be
back soon though.\n< Burdan >

It's surprising when you suddenly start speaking
informally, so could you stop that?\n< Burdan >
You took it, didn't you! Give it back!\n< Serena >
Ah, this thing? Here you go.\n< Burdan >
You can put it on right here if you want?\n< Burdan >

So right now, Serena-san is wearing nothing
underneath...\n< Tim >
Hey, why are you still standing there? Sit down.\n< Burdan >
It's fine. I'll remain standing.\n< Serena >

Really? Then shall we dance? I've been practicing
in my head. I can do better than earlier, you
know?\n< Burdan >
I will not. Do not bother me...!\n< Serena >
What's the matter? You're suddenly in a bad mood?\n< Burdan >
Whose fault do you think it is...!\n< Serena >

You really do get along well, don't you? It's
quite...\n< Tim >

...From what part of our exchange did you get that
impression...\n< Serena >

In front of Tim-dono, at a celebration no less,
I've been holding back.\n< Serena >

But let me be clear on this occasion, I dislike
such frivolous people.\n< Serena >

...That person you dislike... you could do such
things with...?\n< Tim >
Then what am I to you...?\n< Tim >
What's the matter? Are you feeling ill?\n< Serena >

Excuse me... Can we call it a day now? Is that
alright?\n< Tim >
Of course, that's not a problem at all.\n< Serena >
Today was a very... a very enjoyable birthday...\n< Tim >
Both of you, I'm truly... thank you very much...\n< Tim >
Tim-dono, you seemed a bit off towards the end...\n< Serena >

No, of course. It's Tim-dono's birthday and yet
that Burdan...\n< Serena >
To do such a thing in the midst of it all...!\n< Serena >

...I'm terribly sorry for what happened. I hope to
make it up to you someday...\n< Serena >
The plate that had the meat pie on it.\n< Tim >

In the end, Bardan-kun ate it all. It's fine
though...\n< Tim >
